HEADWORD: Callid
<hw>Cal"lid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>callidus</ets>, fr. <ets>callere</ets> to be thick-skinned, to be
hardened, to be practiced, fr. <ets>callum</ets>, <ets>callus</ets>,
callous skin, callosity, callousness.]</ety> <def>Characterized by
cunning or shrewdness; crafty.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Callidity</ent>⟦br⟧
